parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the headlights, taillights, and instrument panel to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the cruise control can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The engine fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the airbags and seatbelts can increase the risk of injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbags and seatbelts not deploying properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to jerk or lunge forward, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels hard or sticky
the pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward when accelerating
the pedal requires excessive force to press
the pedal becomes immovable when trying to depress it from its un-depressed position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: the vehicle continues to idle at high RPMs
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer jumps up and down while the vehicle is in motion

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight connectors can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: headlights require manual adjustment of the connectors to function
